org.javimmutable.collections

Interface Sequence<T>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    InsertableSequence<T>, JImmutableStack<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmptySequenceNode, FilledSequenceNode, JImmutableLinkedStack, MultiValueListNode

    public interface Sequence<T>
    Interface for simple collections that contain a head value and a tail containing the remainder of the sequence.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T getHead()
      Accesses the first value in the Sequence.
      Sequence<T> getTail()
      Accesses the rest of the Sequence.
      boolean isEmpty()
      Determines if this is the end of the Sequence.

    • Method Detail

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Determines if this is the end of the Sequence. When true the Sequence is empty and getHead() cannot be called. getTail() can still be called but will always return an empty Sequence once isEmpty() returns true.

      • getHead

        T getHead()
        Accesses the first value in the Sequence.

      • getTail

        @Nonnull
Sequence<T> getTail()
        Accesses the rest of the Sequence.
